    <header>
      <para styleclass="Heading1">Why do I need to add Geometry to the Base-Part?</para>
    </header>
    <para styleclass="Heading4 Toggle_atocs_">Why do I need to add geometry to the Base-Part?</para>
    <list id="0" type="ol" listtype="decimal" formatstring="&#37;&#48;&#58;&#115;&#46;" format-charset="DEFAULT_CHARSET" levelreset="true" legalstyle="false" startfrom="1" styleclass="Body Text HowTo" style="font-family:&apos;Segoe UI Semibold&apos;; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold; color:#000000;">
      <li styleclass="Body Text HowTo">Why is there not a <text styleclass="Element">CAD-Line</text> in the <link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="MD-POP-BasePart" styleclass="Element">Base-Part</link>?<text styleclass="VariableName">&#32;</text></li>
    </list>
    <para styleclass="Body Text HowTo">We do not want you to automatically add Joints to the Origin of the <text styleclass="Element">Base-Part.</text></para>
    <para styleclass="Body Text HowTo"><text styleclass="Body Text HowTo2">However, you are welcome to do this.</text></para>
    <list id="1" type="ol" listtype="decimal" formatstring="&#37;&#48;&#58;&#115;&#46;" format-charset="DEFAULT_CHARSET" levelreset="true" legalstyle="false" startfrom="2" styleclass="HowTo Numbered" style="font-family:&apos;Segoe UI Semibold&apos;; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold; color:#000000;">
      <li styleclass="HowTo Numbered">Why?<text styleclass="VariableName">&#32;</text></li>
    </list>
    <para styleclass="Body Text HowTo">For the <text styleclass="Element">Base-Part</text>, we have found it to be useful to add <text styleclass="Element">Points</text> and <text styleclass="Element">Lines</text> that are <text style="text-decoration:underline;">not</text> at the Origin or along the X-axis or Y–axis.</para>
    <list id="2" type="ol" listtype="decimal" formatstring="&#37;&#48;&#58;&#115;&#46;" format-charset="DEFAULT_CHARSET" levelreset="true" legalstyle="false" startfrom="3" styleclass="HowTo Numbered" style="font-family:&apos;Segoe UI Semibold&apos;; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold; color:#000000;">
      <li styleclass="HowTo Numbered">Why?<text styleclass="VariableName">&#32;</text></li>
    </list>
    <para styleclass="Body Text HowTo">You can <text style="text-decoration:underline;">edit</text> the dimensions later, and also add the dimensions to a <link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="MD-Command-AddFBDesignSet" styleclass="Element">Design-Set</link>.</para>
    <list id="3" type="ol" listtype="decimal" formatstring="&#37;&#48;&#58;&#115;&#46;" format-charset="DEFAULT_CHARSET" levelreset="true" legalstyle="false" startfrom="4" styleclass="HowTo Numbered" style="font-family:&apos;Segoe UI Semibold&apos;; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold; color:#000000;">
      <li styleclass="HowTo Numbered">Why edit <text styleclass="Element">Points</text> and <text styleclass="Element">Lines</text> in the <text styleclass="Element">Base-Parts</text>?<text styleclass="VariableName">&#32;</text></li>
    </list>
    <list id="4" type="ol" listtype="decimal" formatstring="&#37;&#48;&#58;&#115;&#46;" format-charset="DEFAULT_CHARSET" levelreset="true" legalstyle="false" startfrom="1" styleclass="HowTo Numbered" style="font-family:&apos;Segoe UI Semibold&apos;; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold; color:#000000;">
      <list id="4" level="1" type="ol" listtype="lower-alpha" formatstring="&#37;&#49;&#58;&#115;&#46;" format-charset="DEFAULT_CHARSET" levelreset="true" legalstyle="false" startfrom="1" styleclass="HowTo Numbered" style="font-family:&apos;Segoe UI Semibold&apos;; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold; color:#000000;">
        <li styleclass="HowTo Numbered">Edit the dimension and move the Joints, if the <text styleclass="Element">Points</text> or <text styleclass="Element">Lines</text> are used for Joints<text styleclass="VariableName">&#32;</text></li>
        <li styleclass="HowTo Numbered">Move the <text styleclass="Element">Plane</text> and <text styleclass="Interface">Mechanism-Editor</text> in the Machine Frame, if a <text styleclass="Element">Line</text> is used for a new <text styleclass="Element">Plane</text> and <text styleclass="Interface">Mechanism-Editor</text>.</li>
      </list>
    </list>
